text:
Overall, worth a watch, but it is not memorable. If you like sci-fi like Dunes give it a chance. Don't have huge expectations
The good:Setting is intriguing;
worlds are interesting;
Most actors are pretty damn.good except for protagonist;
some graphics are good;The so-so:
Action scenes are ok;
world-building;
plot-line = premise of finding a whole rebel army to defend a village of 30-40 odd souls? Makes no sense.. village should be of at least several thousand people....
the pacing.The bad:dialogues are poor;
relationships between characters hastily built;
feels like a movie for teenagers;
the protagonist really can't act, not a bit; every line is torture;
some graphics are bad;
in a high-tech world, why are people fighting with clubs and swords?To sum up, worth watching, but it is not memorable. If you like sci-fi like Dunes give it a chance. Don't expect masterpiece.
